				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Odd occurence the other day with Defense skill ups<a name="76089"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 3 05 10:20 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">then they attacked me again and killed me. It happened in less then 8 seconds, and Deftdance should last 18 shouldn't it?</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Lucy Live data shows it at 3 ticks (18 seconds), but I set my timer at 15 seconds <b>MAX</b>.  The reason I do this is to pad any possible lag between client and server.  That 3 ticks is calculated server-side.
<br />

<br />
If you got killed at 8 seconds into deftdance, it may be because you:
<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">ran in to them.</span></blockquote>
<br />
Deftdance will only give you invulnerability in your forward (frontal) arc.  Mobs behind you and possibly even 90 degrees to either side of you will still be able to pound on you.
<br />

<br />
Think of DA as a frontal arc <b>only</b> type of DA.  Now, our DA <b>song</b> will protect 360 degrees all around you.  You can feel free to step in the middle of a swarm with that one.  I still don't (myself) because it gives me the &quot;willies&quot; (shivers).   <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-3.gif" border="0" alt="Scared" hspace="2" />   ...but that's just me, maybe.   <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />  Whether DeftDance <b>or</b> DA song, I still try to only have the mobs in my frontal arc when they are swinging at me.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
